<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>1<percent/> of 2669</li> 
<li>86<percent/> of 43</li> 
<li>28<percent/> of 135</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 28<percent/> of 135</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{86}\%\cdot{43}={36.98}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{28}\%\cdot{135}={37.8}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1}\%\cdot{2669}={26.69}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 28<percent/> of 135 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
